cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on the impact of rumors in Online Social Networks (OSNs) on the performance of device-to-device (D2D) communication. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the vulnerability of D2D communication in the cellular network due to rumors in OSNs. 
3. cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the impact of social networks on D2D communication and proposes a solution to detect critical nodes in the OSN. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the vulnerability of D2D communication in the presence of rumors and proposes a solution to detect critical nodes in the OSN, which can be useful for security purposes. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the impact of rumors in OSNs on the throughput of the cellular network, which involves distributed computing.
